    <briefdescription>
<para>A lightweight identifier for an attachment slot. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="structDali_1_1Ui_1_1AttachmentId" kindref="compound">AttachmentId</ref> values are allocated sequentially via <ref refid="structDali_1_1Ui_1_1AttachmentId_1af394b17796f9469c4550163283141295" kindref="member">AttachmentId::Alloc()</ref>. Allocate one id per logical attachment type and store the returned id in static storage so it can be reused for SetAttachment(), GetAttachment(), and DetachAttachment().</para>
<para>Do not allocate a new id per object instance or per API call. Repeated one-shot allocation wastes the process-wide id space and makes previously stored attachments impossible to retrieve.</para>
<para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>One-time<sp/>allocation<sp/>per<sp/>attachment<sp/>type<sp/>(e.g.<sp/>in<sp/>an<sp/>anonymous<sp/>namespace<sp/>or<sp/>as<sp/>a<sp/>static)</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="keyword">static</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/></highlight><highlight class="keyword">const</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>AttachmentId<sp/>kMyViewDataAttachment<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="structDali_1_1Ui_1_1AttachmentId_1af394b17796f9469c4550163283141295" kindref="member">AttachmentId::Alloc</ref>();</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> </para>
    </detaileddescription>
